FuncDef: The display static-user configuration interface-list command displays information about a specified interface list of static users or all interface lists of static users.

ParaDef.Info:
Specifies the name of an interface list.
The value is a string of 1 to 32 case-insensitive characters.

Examples: <HUAWEI> display static-user configuration interface-list list-name test
ExtraInfo:
Usage Scenario
To locate faults or view information about a specified interface list of static users when the static users fail to go online through interfaces bound to the interface list, run the display static-user configuration interface-list command. If list-name is not specified, brief information about all interface lists of static users is displayed.
Precautions
In VS mode, this command is supported only by the admin VS.
